# Event Emitter module

> Awesome event emitter library with TypeScript support

## Installation
```bash
npm install  @sava_ukr/module-template
```

## Usage
```typescript
import { EventEmitter, delay } from ' @sava_ukr/module-template';

// Create event emitter
const onScoreChange = new EventEmitter<number>();

// Subscribe
const unsubscribe = onScoreChange.subscribe((score) => {
    console.log('Score:', score);
});

// Emit
onScoreChange.emit(100);

// Unsubscribe
unsubscribe();

// Delay utility
await delay(1000);
console.log('1 second later');
```

## API

### EventEmitter<T>

#### Methods

- `subscribe(listener: (data: T) => void): () => void` - Subscribe to events
- `unsubscribe(listener: (data: T) => void): void` - Unsubscribe from events
- `emit(data: T): void` - Emit event
- `clear(): void` - Clear all listeners
- `listenerCount: number` - Get listener count

### delay(ms: number): Promise<void>

Delay execution for specified milliseconds.

